This paper deals with decision-making under uncertainty, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the representation of uncertainty using probability measures, which is a topic in data science (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses regret-based decision-making, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
